caption: This image primarily features lush, vibrant fir branches heavily laden with moisture, possibly dew or raindrops, which emphasize their fresh, green appearance. The branches are densely arranged and overlap one another, creating a depth-filled view with variations in focus. The darker parts of the image in the background suggest low ambient lighting, likely situating this scene in either an early morning or late evening setting, or under thick canopy that diffuses natural light. The fir needles are finely detailed and each droplet of water catches the light, adding a luminescent quality to the image. The photograph does not contain any human activity or man-made objects, reinforcing its natural and serene aesthetic. The image captures the intricate textures and the tranquility of a coniferous forest environment beautifully.
title: Detail of hemlock branches with a new growth.  Green mountain, Washington.  Photo taken near Seattle, Washington.  From the environmental protection agencys project documerica collection, "in praise of forests".  For additional images see fiche #s 209, 210, 211, 212, and 213.
